Italyâ€™s stock market regulator
Consob has asked  Assicurazioni Generali SpA (G)  to supply
information on the terms of its deal with PPF Group NV,  Il Sole
24 Ore  reported, without saying where it got the information.  Generali needs to inform the market before it opens
tomorrow, according to the Italian newspaper. Generali is
evaluating whether to present a report to Consob on the matter,
Il Sole said.  Generali Chairman Cesare Geronzi has been sent a letter by
board members asking him to convene an extraordinary board
meeting, Il Sole reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
